# Framer Motion Builder - Project Structure

This is a Next.js 15 application for prototyping Framer Motion animations with a modern, dark-themed UI.

## Core Architecture

- **Framework**: Next.js 15 with App Router and Turbopack
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS v4 with custom dark theme
- **Animation**: Framer Motion (motion package)
- **UI Components**: Custom components with Radix UI primitives
- **TypeScript**: Full type safety with strict configuration

## Key Files

- [src/app/page.tsx](mdc:src/app/page.tsx) - Main application component with AnimationConfig interface
- [src/app/layout.tsx](mdc:src/app/layout.tsx) - Root layout with IBM Plex fonts and metadata
- [src/components/AnimationControls.tsx](mdc:src/components/AnimationControls.tsx) - Main controls panel
- [src/components/AnimationPreview.tsx](mdc:src/components/AnimationPreview.tsx) - Live animation preview
- [src/types/easings.ts](mdc:src/types/easings.ts) - 60+ easing functions with categories
- [src/types/presets.ts](mdc:src/types/presets.ts) - Animation presets for common patterns

## Component Structure

- **UI Components**: Located in `src/components/ui/` - Reusable UI primitives
- **Feature Components**: Main app components in `src/components/`
- **Types**: TypeScript definitions in `src/types/`
- **Utils**: Utility functions in `src/lib/`

## Animation System

The app uses a centralized `AnimationConfig` interface that defines:
- Animation type (hover, click, loop, onMount)
- Initial and animated property states
- Transition settings (duration, delay, ease)

All animations are built using Framer Motion's `motion` components with real-time preview capabilities.